 broken power-law\nIMF, with a steep slope ($\\alpha_1=$ $3.84$) for stars < 0.5 $M_\\odot$ (as\nsuggested by near-IR indices), and that flattens out ($\\alpha_2=$ $2.14$) for\nstars > 0.5 $M_\\odot$, and discuss its wider ramifications and limitations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Dec 2016 18:53:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-08"}
